Alan Bishop is an American musician best known for being the bassist and vocalist of experimental rock band Sun City Girls.
In the early 1980s Bishop played in the short-lived band Paris 1942 with Maureen Tucker of the Velvet Underground, and was briefly a member of skate punk group JFA.
Bishop is now a member of the Cairo-based band The Invisible Hands.
